column9:
Baidyanath Agnikumar Ras Indigestion, Loss of appetite, Acidity, Colic, Diarrhoea, Dysentery, Cholera \n

Ingredients of Agnikumar Ras

\n
    \n
  • Rasendra Purified and processed Mercury
    • \n
  • Gandhaka Purified and processed Sulphur
    • \n
  • Tankana Purified and processed Borax
    • \n
  • Visha Purified Aconitum ferox
    • \n
  • kaparda Bhasma Bhasma of Cowries
    • \n
  • Shankha Bhasma Conch shell Bhasma
    • \n
  • Maricha Black pepper Piper nigrum
    • \n
\n

Benefits of Agnikumar Ras

\n
    \n
  • Agnikumar Ras is Deepan (increases Pitta), Pachak (kindles digestive fire) medicine working specially on Agni or digestive fire.
    • \n
  • It is especially indicated in Ajeerna, vomiting due to indigestion and jaundice.
    • \n
  • It gives relief in abdominal pain.
    • \n
  • It improves appetite and digestive function.
    • \n
  • It loosen the mucous accumulated in body and gives relief in excess kapha.
    • \n

Key benefits:
\n
\n Acivin (Sandu Audumbaravleha) is a proprietary ayurvedic formulation extremely beneficial for hyperacidity and it's related symptoms.
\n Herbal antacid
\n Helps reduce burning sensation and gives coolant effect to the body.
\n Supportive in the treatment of peptic and duodenal ulcers.
\n Reduces burning sensation of urine, eyes, palms and soles.
\n It helps in reducing excessive thirst.
\n
\nKey Ingredients:
\n
\nAudumbar (Ficus glomerata), Manjishtha (Rubia cordifolia), Sariva (Hemidesmus indicus), Jeerak (Cuminum cyminum), Ela (Elettaria cardemomum)
\n
\nDirection of use:
\n
\n2 teaspoonful (10 ml) 2- 3 times a day

column8: Supportive in Thyroid Dissorders, Anemia, Obesity, Infertility
column9:
Hormonal imbalance is very common and often complicated. Hormones are chemicals secreted by endocrine glands like thyroid, adrenalin, and pituitary. Normal functioning of these endocrine glands maintains balance of hormones. Hormones play significant role in our body. Development of body, metabolic functions, reproduction depends upon normal functioning of these endocrine glands.

Todays lifestyle, lack of exercise, improper diet mental stress affects the normal functioning of the glands. This leads to abnormal (hypo or hyper) secretion of hormones. This is called hormonal imbalance. Today improper functioning of thyroid gland is very common especially in women and adolescent girls.

Hormonal imbalance may lead to several problems in young girls and women like:

Hypothyroidism
PCOD (ovarian disease),
irregular menses,
heavy bleeding and scanty menses,
leucorrhoea (white discharge)
Weight gain,
oedema all over body,
dry skin & dryness of hair,
loss of appetite, sometime constipation, anemia,
lack of concentration
Hyperthyroidism
anxiety,
palpitation,
fatigue,
lethargy,
irritability & anger,
excessive sweating,
irregular menses in women,
depression and occasionally loose motions.
Hormonal imbalance in menopause
Irritability,
depression, worry & mood swings,
continuous minor complaints like body ache,
lack of memory,
incontinence of urine are some symptoms in menopause stage in which hormonal imbalance is present.

column8: It is useful in Chronic constipation, Flatulence, Distention, Discomfort, and heaviness in the abdomen.
column9:
Best natural laxative.Secretion of bile in the liver aids the natural process of bowel movement. Ailments like constipation and irregular or incomplete bowel movement crop up when bile secretion decreases, thus leading to feelings of discomfort and lethargy. Many medicines in the market contain components that enhance bowel movement. If you take these medicines for a prolonged period, the natural ability of the bowels to expand and constrict is lost and you get habituated to it. This can weaken the bowels over time and result in other diseases. Sukhasarak Vati enables the smooth passage of bile and helps in bowel movement, so that your system remains clean.

What does Sukhsarak Vati do? And how is it different form regular laxatives?
Popular Ayurvedic medicines for constipation mainly contain ingredients like Isabgol(Psyllium seed husk) or Senna(Sonamukhi) irritate your intestines specifically the colon responsible for defecation. Thus, even though they do provide temporary relief, frequent use leads to weakening of intestines and can cause dependency and a need to increase the dose gradually.
Sukhsarak Vati is based on a traditional Ayurvedic formula containing a combination of Indravaruni(Citrullus colocynthis) and Haritaki(Terminalia chebula) used to regulate liver function and increase the flow of digestive enzymes.
It also improves the digestion and enhances bowel tone. Thus, it only strengthens the intestinal muscles and brings about defecation naturally.

column9:
Alarsin Aloes Compound is a clinically tested, non-hormonal medicine that helps to regulate menstrual cycles, stimulate ovulation and promote overall menstrual health. This 70 year old ayurvedic formulation offers benefits for menstrual issues such as period cramps, irregular or scanty periods, delayed puberty, infertility and in counteracting the side-effects of contraceptive pills.
\n
\nIn comparison to most herbal products, Alarsin Aloes Compound is not a physical mixture of ayurvedic ingredients but an ayurvedic formulation of 7 ingredients, each in a specific proportion, based on their benefits and efficacy.
\n
\nThe product is convenient, has no side-effects and is safe for use by teenagers, young adults and unmarried women, where intrusive pelvic examinations and hormonal treatment may not be possible or desirable.

column9:
Say goodbye to a blocked nose and coughing throat and enjoy the ease of breathing with Swasamrutham Liquid, an Ayurvedic herbal concoction widely used to treat respiratory tract problems. The amazing natural formulation offers immediate relief in a cough, cold, asthma or any other respiratory problems.

\n

Lauded as a boon for asthmatics, the regular use of SwasamruthamLiquid has shown a drastic decrease in the dependency and frequency of inhalers. This thousand years old treasure of Ayurveda has been tested by time and proven by generations.

\n

In this modernday, Swasamrutham Liquid is considered as one of the best cure for asthma and bronchitis. Packed with the goodness of herbs and plants, the magical syrup helps in combating multiple problems related to the respiratory system. It also helps in eliminating the cause from the source and helps build immunity against diseases.

\n

Ingredients

\n

Adhadhoda vasika, Terminalia chebula, Terminalia bellerica, Piper longum, Abbies webbiana, Piper nigrum, Zingiber officinale, Emblica officinalis, Myristica fragrans

\n

Indications

\n \n
    \n
  • Acute and chronic Bronchitis
    • \n
  • Allergy
    • \n
  • Sinusitis
    • \n
  • Eosinophilla
    • \n
  • Sneezing
    • \n
  • Wheezing
    • \n
  • Cold
    • \n
  • Breathing difficulty
    • \n
  • Acute or chronic cough
    • \n
  • Running nose
    • \n
  • Respiratory diseases
    • \n
\n

Benefits

\n \n
    \n
  • Swasamrutham Liquid eases the airflow to lungs.
    • \n
  • Swasamrutham Liquid helps in preventing asthmatic attacks.
    • \n
  • It reduces inflammation and constriction of the bronchi.
    • \n
  • Swasamrutham Liquid soothes bronchial irritation.
    • \n
  • It alleviates allergic respiratory disorders.
    • \n
  • The herbal syrup is also used to soothe the irritation of cough.
    • \n
  • It works as an expectorant to help reduce cough.
    • \n
  • It strengthens the respiratory system.
    • \n
  • Swasamrutham Liquid is very effective in reducing breathlessness.
    • \n
  • Swasamrutham Liquid is a boon for asthma & bronchitis.
    • \n
\n

Dosage

\n

Adults can take 10 - 15 ml 3 - 4 times a day and for children the recommended dosage is 5 - 10 ml taken 2 - 3 times a day.
